HEADWORD: Tossy
<hw>Toss"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Tossing the head, as in
scorn or pride; hence, proud; contemptuous; scornful; affectedly
indifferent; <as>as, a <ex>tossy</ex> commonplace</as>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>C. Kingsley.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

